 willingness or unwillingness of each movement to find an accommodation based on compromise. Morris assesses the viability and practicality of proposed solutions in the light of complicated and acrimonious realities. Throughout his groundbreaking career, Morris has reshaped understanding of the Israeli-Arab conflict. Here, once again, he arrives at a new way of thinking about the discord, injecting a ray of hope in a region where it is most sorely needed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aArab-Israeli conflictxPeace. 0aIsrael-Arab War, 1948-1949xCauses. 0aIsrael-Arab War, 1948-1949xInfluence. 0aJewish-Arab relationsxHistoryx1917-1948. 0aJewish-Arab relationsxHistoryy1917-1948. 0aPalestinian ArabsxPolitics and government. 0aZionismxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300156041423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300156041.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles